comments.content: A deletion in the chromosomal region 5q35 can cause the rare genetic disorder Sotos syndrome. Sotos syndrome is characterised by psychiatric disorders (autism, intellectual disability, developmental delay) and excessive growth. Also, duplication of 5q35 have been recorded.
